## TL;DR: Everything You Need to Know About Pear Cut Diamonds

A pear cut diamond is a hybrid brilliant-cut shape combining the rounded curve of an oval with the tapered point of a marquise — a single point on one end and a smooth, rounded arc on the other.

It carries 58 facets in the same modified-brilliant family as the round and oval cuts, but its asymmetrical silhouette makes it one of the most distinctive and demanding shapes to evaluate before buying.

**Live price snapshot:**

-   1ct natural G-VS2 Ideal Cut GIA starts at **[$3,150](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28393670?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   1ct natural D-VS1 Ideal Cut GIA: **[$3,810](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29112328?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   2ct natural E-VVS1 Ideal Cut GIA: **[$22,610](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28996100?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   2.51ct natural G-VVS1 Ideal Cut GIA: **[$28,670](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29233964?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   3ct natural D-FL Ideal Cut GIA: **[$93,910](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27216797?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   1.50ct lab-grown D-IF Ideal Cut IGI: **[$3,380](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27421326?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   2.00ct lab-grown D-IF Ideal Cut IGI: **[$5,620](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28761317?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**

**The one thing every pear buyer must know:** A pear diamond has a bow-tie effect, just like an oval — and it also has a vulnerable point that requires specific setting protection.

You cannot evaluate either of these from a GIA certificate or a static photo. You must watch the 360° HD video before purchasing any pear cut diamond, and you must confirm the setting uses a V-prong or protective tip at the point.

**Buy a pear cut if:**

-   You want a shape that visually elongates the finger more dramatically than almost any other cut
-   You want brilliant-cut sparkle in a genuinely distinctive, asymmetrical silhouette
-   You want strong natural diamond value — pear sits below round and oval on a price-per-carat basis at most weights
-   You like the flexibility of wearing it point-up (modern) or point-down (classic) on the hand

**Consider a different shape if:**

-   You want zero asymmetry to worry about — round brilliant
-   You want an elongated shape without a vulnerable point — oval
-   You want a step-cut optical look with long flashes of light instead of brilliant sparkle — emerald

