The 1ct natural pear market is dense and competitive. The floor sits at **[$3,150](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28393670?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** for a G-VS2 Ideal cut — a strong, eye-clean, near-colorless stone.

Moving to D-color VS1 adds roughly $660 (**[$3,810](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29112328?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**), and the data shows color drives most of the price movement in this tier far more than clarity does — VS2 to VS1 within the same color typically adds only $100–200, while moving from G to D color at the same clarity can add $500–700.

My recommendation at 1ct: G or H color with VS2 clarity is the value sweet spot. At **[$3,150](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28393670?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**, you get a stone that is eye-clean and reads colorless to the naked eye in a white metal setting — the D-to-G premium buys you a paper distinction, not a visible one, in a brilliant-cut shape like pear.

