This is a genuinely important finding: at exactly 2.00ct, Blue Nile's live pear inventory is thin — only two listings, both at premium color and clarity (E-VVS1 and F-VS1). I call this **The 2-Carat Pear Gap**.

Compare this to the 24 listings at 1.00ct above. What this means practically: if you want a 2ct pear at a moderate color/clarity combination (say, G-VS2, similar to the best 1ct value), you likely won't find it sitting exactly at 2.00ct — you'll need to shop the 2.5ct+ tier below, or accept paying for VVS1/VS1 grades you don't necessarily need.

This thin-inventory pattern at the round-number 2ct mark is worth knowing before you start shopping, because it changes your search strategy.

