rmational">$57,920</a></strong></td></tr><tr><td>GIA</td><td>2.70ct</td><td>D</td><td>IF</td><td>Ideal</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28110800?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational">$58,310</a></strong></td></tr><tr><td>GIA</td><td>2.80ct</td><td>E</td><td>IF</td><td>Ideal</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/25132372?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational">$60,420</a></strong></td></tr><tr><td>GIA</td><td>2.91ct</td><td>G</td><td>VVS1</td><td>Ideal</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28242987?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational">$60,610</a></strong></td></tr><tr><td>GIA</td><td>2.85ct</td><td>D</td><td>IF</td><td>Ideal</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/20704833?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational">$81,240</a></strong></td></tr></tbody></table>

The data here makes **The Scaling Tax** unmistakable. Moving from 1ct (**[$3,150](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28393670?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** floor) to 2.51ct (**[$28,670](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29233964?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** floor) is a 2.5x weight increase for a 9x price increase.

This is not unique to pear — every diamond shape scales exponentially past 1–2ct because larger rough stones are exponentially rarer — but the magnitude is worth seeing in real numbers before you shop this tier.

Within this tier, the G-VVS1 at **[$28,670](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29233964?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** versus the D-VVS1 at **[$39,960](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28674278?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** — both essentially the same carat weight, same clarity — shows an $11,290 premium purely for color (G to D).

At this carat weight in a pear cut, that color jump is largely invisible to the naked eye in a white metal setting. The G-VVS1 is the stronger value position.

![Pear cut diamond scaling tax infographic — price-per-carat chart from 1ct to 3ct natural pear showing the exponential cost curve with real Blue Nile price data](/images/pear-cut-diamond-scaling-tax.avif)

*The Scaling Tax in pear diamonds: 1ct → 2.5ct is 2.5× the weight but 9× the price. The G-VVS1 at 2.51ct is the strongest value entry into the 2ct+ natural pear tier. **[See this 2.51ct G-VVS1 Ideal GIA pear on Blue Nile →](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29233964?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)***

