At this tier, the F-VS1 at **[$46,480](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28435605?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** is the strongest value entry point into 3ct+ pear. Compare it to the D-FL at the top of the table — **[$119,400](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28639663?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** for 3.52ct — and you're looking at a 2.5x price difference for a color and clarity distinction that is genuinely undetectable to the naked eye in a brilliant-cut pear of this size.

This is the same FL/IF tax pattern that appears across every shape: spectacular on paper, invisible in person.

